        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"170348\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Any recommendations for a beaujolais made with no carbonic maceration?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The question has been somewhat confused by the fact that in the Beaujolais folks have for some time taken to calling traditional whole bunch vinification with crushing \u201csemi-carbonic maceration\u201d.</p>\n<p>In addition to Bouland, I would recommend Louis-Claude Desvignes, Ch\u00e2teau Thivin, Jean-Paul Brun, Chermette, Jean-Marc Burgaud - and plenty of others.</p>",
